This order was absolutely horrendous - it’s not even fit for consumption. Let’s start with the fact that I asked for the pizza to be square cut online when ordering. I get there and it’s regular cut. The young lady at the register asks if I’d like it cut square I say yes. She hands it to the person in the back and she begins mumbling and cutting again - I mention that I did indicate online for square cut - the young lady agrees. The pizza is given bs k to me I get home and it’s now in these extra thin triangles. I still make an attempt at eating a slice but there’s soooooooooooo much garlic and sooooooooooo little sauce that it’s inedible. Not to forget that I asked for half sausage and half spinach/green peppers so even if I could attempt to have eaten it - the order still went correct. What a waste of my time and money I am HIGHLY displeased and disappointed. I called to speak with a manager a young lady was placed on the phone - I explained my issue. She stated to bring the pizza back and she’d make a new one - I explained to her that not only could I not tonight but that even if I could I do not want ANYTHING else from them ever. She advised I could bring it the next day and stated who to ask for and that they “should be able to credit me” I asked if she SHOULD be able to REFUND me or if she WOULD be able to - as I only had not even half of a slice of the pizza. She stated that she could and when I then asked who I was speaking with she stated Myra which is the same person she said SHOULD be able to credit me. I felt she was extremely rude and dismissive. I will never again patronize this establishment.
